@startuml admin-layout-structure
!theme plain
title Admin Application - Layout Structure

skinparam componentStyle rectangle

component "App.vue" as App

package "Router (/admin)" {
    [Login View] as Login
    [Forbidden View] as Forbidden

    package "Admin Layout" {
        [AdminLayout.vue] as Layout

        package "Topbar" {
            [AdminTopbar.vue] as Topbar
        }

        package "Sidebar" {
            [AdminSidebar.vue] as Sidebar
        }

        [router-view] as RouterView
    }
}

App --> Login : /admin/login
App --> Forbidden : /admin/forbidden
App --> Layout : /admin/* (protected)

Layout --> Topbar
Layout --> Sidebar
Layout --> RouterView

package "Admin Views" {
    [Dashboard.vue] as Dashboard
    [Users/UserList.vue] as UserList
    [Users/UserDetails.vue] as UserDetails
    [Plans/PlanList.vue] as PlanList
    [Analytics/Dashboard.vue] as Analytics
}

RouterView --> Dashboard : /admin/
RouterView --> UserList : /admin/users
RouterView --> UserDetails : /admin/users/:id
RouterView --> PlanList : /admin/plans
RouterView --> Analytics : /admin/analytics

note right of Layout
  **AdminLayout Structure**

  ┌────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Topbar                         │
  ├────────┬───────────────────────┤
  │        │                       │
  │ Side-  │  Main Content         │
  │ bar    │  <router-view />      │
  │        │                       │
  │        │                       │
  └────────┴───────────────────────┘
end note

note bottom of Sidebar
  Navigation items dynamically
  highlight based on current route.

  Each item links to plugin routes:
  - Dashboard → /admin/
  - Users → /admin/users
  - Plans → /admin/plans
  etc.
end note

note left of Topbar
  Topbar components:
  1. Branding/Title
  2. Global search
  3. Notifications (future)
  4. User dropdown
     - Logout
     - Profile (future)
end note

@enduml
